WEBVTT

00:00:00.055 --> 00:00:01.755
(Child actors were accompanied by a guardian...)

00:00:01.755 --> 00:00:03.117
(and filmed in a safe, supervised environment.)

00:00:05.625 --> 00:00:08.295
My gosh, what's wrong with them? What's their deal?

00:00:10.765 --> 00:00:12.905
- What? What's going on? - Auntie.

00:00:14.070 --> 00:00:15.070
What?

00:00:16.475 --> 00:00:18.545
(Episode 9)

00:00:29.355 --> 00:00:31.085
What should we do?

00:00:46.335 --> 00:00:48.105
Do something, quick.

00:00:48.475 --> 00:00:51.705
- Let's get out and stop them. - Okay.

00:01:00.445 --> 00:01:02.785
- That woman... Wait. - What's wrong?

00:01:03.055 --> 00:01:04.385
(Police)

00:01:09.525 --> 00:01:10.965
Hello, Ms. Yang.

00:01:11.225 --> 00:01:14.025
- You scared me. What is it, Chief? - Well...

00:01:14.095 --> 00:01:15.095
Hello.

00:01:16.195 --> 00:01:20.135
- What's going on? - I'm sorry about last time.

00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:22.375
- Yes. - You're sorry? For what?

00:01:23.275 --> 00:01:24.875
I'm a little busy right now.

00:01:25.505 --> 00:01:28.175
- No! Wait! - My goodness. Just a moment.

00:01:28.545 --> 00:01:30.275
I said I'm busy. What do you think you're doing?

00:01:30.715 --> 00:01:32.715
It's just that...

00:01:33.515 --> 00:01:35.755
- If that's all, I'll be going now. - No.

00:01:35.815 --> 00:01:37.185
I don't know your circumstances, but...

00:01:37.555 --> 00:01:39.185
- I really wanted to help you. - Go!

00:01:39.855 --> 00:01:41.595
- But according to regulations, - Excuse me?

00:01:42.055 --> 00:01:45.095
- we can't look up plates on a whim. - Right.

00:01:45.165 --> 00:01:47.665
We've talked about this before. You said you couldn't, right?

00:01:47.735 --> 00:01:49.035
You told me to file an official report.

00:01:49.095 --> 00:01:51.705
Right. But we're still trying to find a way, no matter what.

00:01:51.705 --> 00:01:53.935
- Go! - We're trying everything we can.

00:01:54.005 --> 00:01:56.105
- Let's go. - It's fine. Please step aside.

00:01:56.175 --> 00:01:57.205
- Ma'am... - Wait.

00:01:57.335 --> 00:01:59.375
We're stepping up patrols in the area.

00:01:59.775 --> 00:02:01.315
You haven't had any trouble, have you?

00:02:01.945 --> 00:02:05.685
- No, none. Are we done here? - Is that so?

00:02:06.985 --> 00:02:08.385
All right. Thank you for your cooperation.

00:02:08.985 --> 00:02:11.025
- Take care now. - Have a good day.

00:02:11.885 --> 00:02:13.155
(Police)

00:02:13.285 --> 00:02:14.595
What was that about? Seriously.

00:02:26.735 --> 00:02:27.735
Unbelievable.

00:02:28.275 --> 00:02:29.675
I almost caught them.

00:02:52.768 --> 00:02:57.038
- That was a close call. - I know. My heart's racing.

00:02:57.468 --> 00:02:59.508
Man, what would've happened if we hadn't come by on our patrol?

00:02:59.568 --> 00:03:03.638
I know, right? But I thought those two ran off together.

00:03:03.838 --> 00:03:05.508
What are they doing carrying on like that here in Onjeong?

00:03:05.578 --> 00:03:07.008
That's what I'm saying.

00:03:07.378 --> 00:03:10.848
How can they be so bold in broad daylight?

00:03:11.178 --> 00:03:14.448
- Unbelievable, really. - Should we go back one last time?

00:03:16.718 --> 00:03:17.718
Hurry.

00:03:22.298 --> 00:03:25.298
Darling, the police helped us on purpose, right?

00:03:25.368 --> 00:03:28.768
They did. It's like the heavens are blessing our love.

00:03:35.238 --> 00:03:37.638
- Ju Ah. - Hyun Bin.

00:03:37.978 --> 00:03:40.108
Love blessed by the heavens? Give me a break.

00:03:40.708 --> 00:03:42.748
If the heavens knew, they'd strike you down.

00:03:47.018 --> 00:03:51.288
Look, I get that people have affairs sometimes.

00:03:52.358 --> 00:03:53.888
With another woman's husband, a father.

00:03:54.328 --> 00:03:57.598
Fine. You make your own bed, you lie in it. What do I care?

00:03:57.928 --> 00:04:02.398
- With that family of all people? - Keep your voice down, will you?

00:04:02.898 --> 00:04:05.108
Do you have any idea how much this is going to hurt our families?

00:04:05.438 --> 00:04:09.078
Do you have no clue what will happen if our fathers find out?

00:04:09.938 --> 00:04:13.408
I've already taken an earful from my mother-in-law and sister-in-law.

00:04:14.178 --> 00:04:15.548
Grandma and Mom?

00:04:15.918 --> 00:04:17.818
They know who you're having an affair with?

00:04:18.148 --> 00:04:20.448
Yes. Everyone knows but my husband.

00:04:22.918 --> 00:04:27.528
I agreed to take money for a divorce and keep it from the families.

00:04:29.428 --> 00:04:31.898
So that's why they offered you money.

00:04:32.768 --> 00:04:35.638
- Right. - Then you should've left this town.

00:04:36.098 --> 00:04:39.338
Why make a scene in Onjeong in public? What if you're seen?

00:04:39.538 --> 00:04:42.308
His wife won't grant him a divorce.

00:04:42.908 --> 00:04:45.478
Yong Gil told me to go on to Ganghwa and wait for him,

00:04:46.108 --> 00:04:47.708
so we were just saying our goodbyes.

00:04:47.978 --> 00:04:49.218
Please.

00:04:49.578 --> 00:04:51.418
You're making me sick. I can't listen to this anymore.

00:04:52.018 --> 00:04:53.648
To think my uncle called a woman like you his wife.

00:04:55.718 --> 00:04:59.528
My poor uncle is the fool here, treating you so delicately.

00:05:00.858 --> 00:05:01.928
Honestly.

00:05:12.408 --> 00:05:14.878
Didn't you know she was from Dr. Gong's family?

00:05:16.408 --> 00:05:18.148
Not at first, no.

00:05:19.208 --> 00:05:22.018
Once I found out, I swear I tried to keep my distance.

00:05:23.148 --> 00:05:24.578
But the more I tried,

00:05:25.448 --> 00:05:26.818
the more it felt like fate.

00:05:27.688 --> 00:05:29.288
Like we were Romeo and Juliet.

00:05:29.958 --> 00:05:31.288
Don't you ever think about your son?

00:05:31.788 --> 00:05:34.528
Ji Hu is all grown up. He'll be fine with it.

00:05:35.428 --> 00:05:39.628
Hyun Bin, your parents got divorced when you were his age, right?

00:05:40.068 --> 00:05:44.468
But look how well you turned out. I hope Ji Hu looks up to you.

00:05:46.568 --> 00:05:47.738
This is so annoying.

00:05:50.608 --> 00:05:52.908
Does her family know about this?

00:05:53.778 --> 00:05:56.548
Well, the old lady at the pharmacy,

00:05:57.148 --> 00:05:59.018
Dr. Han Seong Mi,

00:05:59.818 --> 00:06:01.288
and her son in med school are probably the only ones.

00:06:05.158 --> 00:06:06.558
Why did you meet with Councillor Hwang?

00:06:07.088 --> 00:06:10.458
What did you say that made him cancel the golf outing?

00:06:10.698 --> 00:06:13.768
You fool. Your problem is that you always blame someone else.

00:06:13.828 --> 00:06:17.298
How is this blaming someone else? You're the one who blew a sure deal.

00:06:17.398 --> 00:06:21.338
Please. "A sure deal?" It wasn't even close.

00:06:22.008 --> 00:06:25.978
Councillor Hwang never even considered you for the nomination.

00:06:26.848 --> 00:06:30.878
- Is that really true? - Of course. Why would he pick you?

00:06:31.248 --> 00:06:34.958
To a corner-cutter who pulls tricks and even forges documents.

00:06:35.618 --> 00:06:39.228
See? I knew it. You went to him and bad-mouthed me.

00:06:39.528 --> 00:06:40.688
What's your endgame here?

00:06:41.088 --> 00:06:43.298
Don't tell me you're after my city council seat too.

00:06:43.558 --> 00:06:47.268
Hey. You're seriously paranoid.

00:06:47.328 --> 00:06:48.868
You should get some professional help.

00:06:48.938 --> 00:06:53.038
Why do you think I'm like this? You took everything from me.

00:06:53.138 --> 00:06:55.978
Hey. Since you brought it up, let's settle this once and for all.

00:06:56.238 --> 00:06:58.008
What exactly have I ever taken from you?

00:06:58.348 --> 00:07:01.878
You got my father's vote in exchange for treating him!

00:07:02.248 --> 00:07:03.318
What?

00:07:03.748 --> 00:07:04.918
You've got to be kidding me.

00:07:05.548 --> 00:07:09.218
Fine, whatever. So what else did I take from you?

00:07:09.418 --> 00:07:13.258
You knew full well I liked Seong Mi, but you dated her anyway.

00:07:13.388 --> 00:07:17.498
No, you fool. You were the one who liked my girlfriend.

00:07:17.558 --> 00:07:20.868
What about your dad seducing my mom and running off with her?

00:07:22.238 --> 00:07:25.668
You jerk. Are you spouting any nonsense that comes to mind now?

00:07:25.738 --> 00:07:28.408
- Hey! Why are you fighting again? - This is unbelievable.

00:07:28.408 --> 00:07:30.278
Let go! Talk it out!

00:07:30.708 --> 00:07:33.078
You're grown men. Why are you still fighting this way?

00:07:33.408 --> 00:07:36.218
Why not? Then you might as well take that video of me on my knees...

00:07:36.278 --> 00:07:37.648
and leak it to the whole town?

00:07:38.048 --> 00:07:40.048
Go on, show everyone how you used your power...

00:07:40.048 --> 00:07:42.418
to make a desperate man kneel and how you filmed it...

00:07:42.418 --> 00:07:44.818
to blackmail him. Go ahead and play it for everyone!

00:07:45.428 --> 00:07:48.698
Because the only thing it'll do is expose your true colours.

00:07:48.998 --> 00:07:50.428
(Onjeong Market Merchants' Association)

00:07:50.498 --> 00:07:51.498
That jerk...

00:07:52.428 --> 00:07:55.498
No, wait. He's got a point.

00:07:56.268 --> 00:07:57.598
You really can't let that get out.

00:08:00.638 --> 00:08:05.378
Who's he to lecture me on character? That jerk!

00:08:05.848 --> 00:08:06.878
Darn it.

00:08:08.048 --> 00:08:11.118
"Dr. Yang has a bad personality. Basically, he's not very likeable."

00:08:11.418 --> 00:08:12.618
That's what he said.

00:08:14.748 --> 00:08:17.418
Oh, my. That's a total misunderstanding.

00:08:17.618 --> 00:08:20.128
Someone is clearly trying to slander him.

00:08:20.388 --> 00:08:22.798
In any case, a full day of golf...

00:08:23.298 --> 00:08:25.098
He said it felt like too much of a commitment.

00:08:25.428 --> 00:08:29.398
A shame, after he worked so hard to become the vice president.

00:08:31.068 --> 00:08:34.408
But you know I'm not one to give up so easily.

00:08:35.108 --> 00:08:37.878
Please, could you put me in touch with his wife?

00:08:38.608 --> 00:08:41.148
If you're uncomfortable giving me her number,

00:08:41.448 --> 00:08:44.078
then just let me join you next time you see her.

00:08:44.148 --> 00:08:46.218
That might be a little difficult.

00:08:51.158 --> 00:08:54.828
Atelier Vertige Eau de Toilette.

00:08:55.598 --> 00:08:59.498
When I tried a sample of this, I immediately thought of you.

00:08:59.928 --> 00:09:03.038
I'm having brunch with his wife sometime this week.

00:09:03.168 --> 00:09:04.238
I'll let you know.

00:09:05.208 --> 00:09:07.038
I'll be waiting for your call.

00:09:14.378 --> 00:09:15.618
What about the Cabanel bag?

00:09:15.948 --> 00:09:19.948
- I returned it to the rental place. - What? Why did you send it back?

00:09:20.248 --> 00:09:23.388
What do you mean, why? It was rented, so I returned it.

00:09:23.488 --> 00:09:27.788
But you got money from Grandfather! You could've paid it off...

00:09:27.858 --> 00:09:29.798
and just kept the bag!

00:09:29.798 --> 00:09:32.268
It's limited-edition. You know it's hard to find!

00:09:32.328 --> 00:09:36.838
Gosh, listen, I have a bad headache. Let's drop it for now, sweetie.

00:09:37.038 --> 00:09:39.008
Would you treat me like this if I were your real daughter?

00:09:39.108 --> 00:09:41.908
- Yes, I would. - Liar!

00:09:42.378 --> 00:09:44.478
- You're done talking, right? - Wait!

00:09:44.538 --> 00:09:45.548
Se Ri!

00:09:46.908 --> 00:09:49.348
Se Ri, wait! I need to talk to you. Just for a second.

00:09:50.778 --> 00:09:52.588
Gosh, that Cabanel bag...

00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:56.918
My goodness. So? Did you see the woman's face?

00:09:57.118 --> 00:10:00.558
No, I only saw her from behind. A police car blocked my view.

00:10:00.888 --> 00:10:03.058
If they met at the playground right after the call...

00:10:03.798 --> 00:10:06.768
- She must be from Onjeong. - Who in the world could it be?

00:10:07.368 --> 00:10:09.468
Could it be some woman he met near work?

00:10:09.938 --> 00:10:13.468
Now we know she's from Onjeong, I'll have my people identify her.

00:10:15.108 --> 00:10:17.678
If I ever get my hands on that witch,

00:10:18.238 --> 00:10:19.678
I'm going to tear her life apart.

00:10:22.148 --> 00:10:23.548
Darling, did you get home safe?

00:10:23.848 --> 00:10:26.548
Just wait a little longer. I'll get a divorce and come to you.

00:10:34.658 --> 00:10:36.098
I have something to tell you.

00:10:37.598 --> 00:10:39.628
I'm seeing someone else.

00:10:40.798 --> 00:10:41.868
So what?

00:10:42.238 --> 00:10:43.698
I want a divorce!

00:10:43.768 --> 00:10:46.208
How dare you ask for a divorce when you're the one who cheated?

00:10:46.708 --> 00:10:49.508
Dong Suk, please just let me go.

00:10:49.578 --> 00:10:51.748
You don't love me either.

00:10:52.378 --> 00:10:53.548
Who is this witch?

00:10:54.178 --> 00:10:57.218
- Why do you need to know? - I'm going to sue her for adultery.

00:10:57.218 --> 00:10:58.348
What?

00:10:58.348 --> 00:11:01.988
She has to pay the price for wrecking a family, right?

00:11:08.998 --> 00:11:10.758
Darn it.

00:11:13.628 --> 00:11:17.538
- Gong Woo Jae. - You scared me. You should knock.

00:11:17.598 --> 00:11:21.668
Why didn't you say our aunt's lover is from Dr. Yang's clinic?

00:11:22.738 --> 00:11:24.438
How did you find that out?

00:11:24.508 --> 00:11:27.748
How do you think I found out? I saw them in daylight, so close...

00:11:27.948 --> 00:11:31.378
- Getting all handsy. Gosh, really. - What?

00:11:32.218 --> 00:11:34.718
Hui Gyeong is still in Onjeong?

00:11:36.588 --> 00:11:39.128
It's a huge relief that you saw them and not his family.

00:11:39.328 --> 00:11:41.388
I wasn't alone. I was with the Director.

00:11:41.928 --> 00:11:44.128
The Director? You mean Bucket's son?

00:11:44.198 --> 00:11:46.728
Yes. He was visiting his family.

00:11:46.728 --> 00:11:48.598
We were in his car together when we saw them.

00:11:49.098 --> 00:11:51.938
He called me and said he'd handle it so it doesn't blow up.

00:11:51.968 --> 00:11:56.508
It can't get out of hand. If the dads find out, it'll be war.

00:11:57.008 --> 00:12:00.708
- So only Dad and Uncle don't know? - Right.

00:12:00.778 --> 00:12:03.018
Darn it. What the... Guys, you scared me.

00:12:03.378 --> 00:12:05.118
What's everyone doing in my room?

00:12:05.188 --> 00:12:07.748
Does anyone here ever knock? Seriously.

00:12:07.888 --> 00:12:10.288
Why would I knock to come into my own room?

00:12:10.358 --> 00:12:11.688
Why did you come home so early?

00:12:11.688 --> 00:12:13.188
You said the association was keeping you busy.

00:12:13.258 --> 00:12:16.028
He got into a huge fight with Bucket.

00:12:16.098 --> 00:12:19.398
- They fought? But why? - Is there a family problem?

00:12:19.498 --> 00:12:21.628
Just because I met with Councillor Hwang,

00:12:21.628 --> 00:12:24.268
that jerk had a huge fit.

00:12:27.438 --> 00:12:30.438
- I have to go somewhere. - Me too.

00:12:30.508 --> 00:12:32.148
- Hey, wait. - Oh, I wonder what Mother is up to.

00:12:32.148 --> 00:12:33.848
- Hear me out. Hey! - Mother!

00:12:33.848 --> 00:12:35.848
This is so unfair, I can't even... I'm so furious...

00:12:36.848 --> 00:12:40.688
- Gosh, I can't believe this. - It's okay. I've got your back.

00:12:41.688 --> 00:12:43.558
You saw the whole thing, didn't you?

00:12:44.888 --> 00:12:47.658
He looked utterly flustered when I said that.

00:12:48.158 --> 00:12:50.428
You really should have seen the look on his face.

00:12:50.528 --> 00:12:53.498
Darling, you're so clever.

00:12:53.628 --> 00:12:56.068
I thought the video of you kneeling...

00:12:56.068 --> 00:12:58.608
would only put you at a disadvantage.

00:12:59.108 --> 00:13:02.478
I guess I'm just a fool who can't see the big picture.

00:13:03.638 --> 00:13:06.508
Have you tried getting in touch with Councillor Hwang's people again?

00:13:06.878 --> 00:13:08.178
Why did he cancel the golf outing?

00:13:08.718 --> 00:13:13.648
- Well, he had a headache. - What a shame.

00:13:14.318 --> 00:13:17.558
He was very apologetic and insisted we reschedule.

00:13:17.788 --> 00:13:20.328
This won't affect our special plan whatsoever.

00:13:20.388 --> 00:13:22.158
It's just a tiny little hiccup,

00:13:22.428 --> 00:13:23.628
so let's not overreact.

00:13:23.628 --> 00:13:26.298
Save this golf outfit for another day.

00:13:27.698 --> 00:13:28.698
Is that right?

00:13:29.238 --> 00:13:31.398
You think I was too hard on Jeong Han?

00:13:31.498 --> 00:13:35.878
No, you did the right thing, honey. He needs a reminder of his place.

00:13:36.378 --> 00:13:37.438
That's true.

00:13:38.908 --> 00:13:41.248
My, it's Hyun Bin.

00:13:43.278 --> 00:13:44.318
Son.

00:13:45.218 --> 00:13:48.218
You should've just come home. Why did you want to meet out here?

00:13:50.858 --> 00:13:52.728
Earlier, near our house,

00:13:53.528 --> 00:13:55.058
I saw Uncle.

00:13:57.028 --> 00:13:58.028
Oh, wait...

00:13:58.828 --> 00:14:01.868
With another woman?

00:14:02.398 --> 00:14:03.898
So you already knew.

00:14:06.208 --> 00:14:07.268
By any chance...

00:14:08.308 --> 00:14:09.538
Did you see who she was?

00:14:13.608 --> 00:14:15.278
It was Uncle Dae Han's wife.

00:14:16.048 --> 00:14:17.048
Who?

00:14:17.578 --> 00:14:18.588
The one from the clinic.

00:14:22.988 --> 00:14:23.988
My gosh!

00:14:24.858 --> 00:14:25.858
I can't believe it.

00:14:26.458 --> 00:14:27.728
Her? That ditzy woman?

00:14:28.128 --> 00:14:31.158
My goodness. No way. How could he possibly be with her?

00:14:31.258 --> 00:14:32.798
What are we going to do? This is unbelievable.

00:14:34.068 --> 00:14:35.538
What about her husband?

00:14:36.068 --> 00:14:37.238
Does that family know?

00:14:37.898 --> 00:14:40.968
According to Uncle, the pharmacist and Dr. Han...

00:14:41.138 --> 00:14:42.608
went all the way to Ganghwa to see them.

00:14:44.208 --> 00:14:45.348
Ganghwa?

00:14:45.548 --> 00:14:48.248
Doctor, what brings you here?

00:14:50.048 --> 00:14:51.918
The public health center here...

00:14:52.588 --> 00:14:55.488
asked me to run a mental health program.

00:14:57.118 --> 00:14:58.758
I'm just speechless.

00:14:59.328 --> 00:15:02.058
How could she lie so brazenly like that?

00:15:02.298 --> 00:15:04.728
Maybe she just didn't want us to find out.

00:15:05.158 --> 00:15:07.528
Apparently, Uncle Dae Han and Dr. Gong don't know either.

00:15:09.068 --> 00:15:10.868
That's a relief, at least.

00:15:12.408 --> 00:15:14.008
Anyway, son...

00:15:14.908 --> 00:15:17.138
You absolutely did the right thing by telling me.

00:15:18.238 --> 00:15:19.578
What are you going to do?

00:15:19.778 --> 00:15:22.078
I'll have to end this quietly. Without a soul finding out.

00:15:22.478 --> 00:15:24.778
Absolutely no one can know about this.

00:15:25.118 --> 00:15:26.988
If your grandfather, father, and aunt were to find out,

00:15:27.318 --> 00:15:29.218
can you imagine how devastated they would be?

00:15:29.988 --> 00:15:33.488
I'm sorry for dumping this on you when I can't even fix it myself.

00:15:33.588 --> 00:15:35.798
What? Don't say that.

00:15:36.758 --> 00:15:38.298
As the lady of the Yang house,

00:15:38.598 --> 00:15:40.428
it's my responsibility to handle these things.

00:15:41.068 --> 00:15:43.698
I'm so grateful to you, for so many reasons.

00:15:45.638 --> 00:15:46.938
Hey, then...

00:15:48.368 --> 00:15:51.638
Could I ask you for a favour?

00:15:52.948 --> 00:15:54.248
Yes, of course. Anything.

00:16:01.948 --> 00:16:05.058
Thank you. I didn't even realise I left it.

00:16:05.388 --> 00:16:08.528
- What happened? - I told her to leave for good.

00:16:08.828 --> 00:16:12.898
- What about you? - I asked my stepmother for help.

00:16:13.498 --> 00:16:15.398
Are you sure that was a good idea?

00:16:15.868 --> 00:16:18.738
She'll handle it. She's the person I trust the most.

00:16:19.368 --> 00:16:20.368
Okay.

00:16:21.368 --> 00:16:25.038
Should we get back to where we left off?

00:16:27.208 --> 00:16:29.948
Well... Where were we again?

00:16:30.918 --> 00:16:33.218
Right. That you hate the idea of me on a blind date,

00:16:33.518 --> 00:16:36.688
and you can't stand seeing me smile at other guys.

00:16:36.958 --> 00:16:38.318
That's as far as you got.

00:16:40.188 --> 00:16:41.688
When I was in Argentina,

00:16:42.098 --> 00:16:43.758
do you know why I never got in touch?

00:16:44.758 --> 00:16:48.398
I just figured you'd met some pretty blonde girl.

00:16:52.608 --> 00:16:54.208
I didn't have the confidence.

00:16:55.238 --> 00:16:58.538
I didn't think there was a future for us.

00:16:59.848 --> 00:17:00.848
A future?

00:17:01.148 --> 00:17:03.948
Wait, you were already thinking about a future back then?

00:17:04.518 --> 00:17:05.518
I was.

00:17:06.388 --> 00:17:10.318
What kind of house we'd live in, whether to have a son or a daughter.

00:17:10.718 --> 00:17:12.588
Oh, my goodness.

00:17:12.958 --> 00:17:14.188
Isn't that a given?

00:17:14.528 --> 00:17:17.328
When you're in love, you naturally want to be together.

00:17:17.328 --> 00:17:18.498
You dream about getting married, having kids,

00:17:18.498 --> 00:17:20.228
and building a happy future together.

00:17:20.668 --> 00:17:23.598
Well, I guess that's true, but...

00:17:25.468 --> 00:17:26.538
But...

00:17:27.968 --> 00:17:31.878
Back then, I was so ashamed of my family.

00:17:32.508 --> 00:17:34.208
With a family that even I couldn't stand,

00:17:34.608 --> 00:17:37.278
I just couldn't bring myself to ask you to be a part of them.

00:17:42.118 --> 00:17:45.688
Earlier, my stepmother asked me for a favour.

00:17:47.458 --> 00:17:49.458
My grandfather and father had a fight,

00:17:49.898 --> 00:17:52.128
and she asked me to help them make up.

00:17:53.768 --> 00:17:57.438
Normally, I'd hate the thought of doing that, but I agreed to help.

00:17:58.238 --> 00:18:00.438
This family of mine that I'm so ashamed of...

00:18:01.208 --> 00:18:03.238
I've decided I want to try and change them.

00:18:04.778 --> 00:18:09.018
I'm going to rebrand my family. For you, Gong Ju Ah.

00:18:10.918 --> 00:18:14.588
You showed up right in front of me when I got back to Korea,

00:18:14.888 --> 00:18:18.118
and we ended up at the same company. I think it's all destiny.

00:18:19.428 --> 00:18:21.688
I've been trying to deny it and run from it,

00:18:23.198 --> 00:18:25.498
but I can't hide my feelings anymore.

00:18:27.198 --> 00:18:30.338
It's a fact that our families despise each other,

00:18:30.998 --> 00:18:34.468
but I'm going to try to overcome it, if you're okay with that.

00:18:36.678 --> 00:18:39.278
No, I mean... It's just...

00:18:39.348 --> 00:18:42.378
I've never thought about anything like this before.

00:18:42.548 --> 00:18:45.318
I know this is sudden. And I know it's a lot to take in.

00:18:45.788 --> 00:18:48.318
Take all the time you need to think about it.

00:18:52.258 --> 00:18:55.798
And I prepared this earlier today.

00:18:56.828 --> 00:18:57.858
Please give this to your uncle.

00:18:58.998 --> 00:19:00.168
My gosh.

00:19:15.408 --> 00:19:16.548
You should have some, too.

00:19:20.418 --> 00:19:22.988
If you don't eat well while dieting, you'll lose muscle,

00:19:23.058 --> 00:19:24.218
your metabolic hormones will be imbalanced,

00:19:24.288 --> 00:19:25.558
and it can weaken your immune system.

00:19:26.658 --> 00:19:31.158
You sound like a real doctor. It's so cool.

00:19:32.598 --> 00:19:34.928
Do you only like me because I'm going to be a doctor?

00:19:34.998 --> 00:19:37.938
Or are you pretending to like me to get on your stepmom's nerves?

00:19:42.508 --> 00:19:44.838
What's your first-ever memory?

00:19:45.578 --> 00:19:47.108
- Out of the blue? - Yes.

00:19:50.818 --> 00:19:51.978
I remember...

00:19:52.518 --> 00:19:56.758
I was five? I got hit by a ball watching older kids play.

00:20:00.528 --> 00:20:03.058
Mine's from first grade,

00:20:03.828 --> 00:20:05.558
on a drizzly spring day.

00:20:06.328 --> 00:20:09.168
I put on my raincoat to go to school and stepped outside,

00:20:09.238 --> 00:20:12.708
and there was this giant earthworm right in front of the gate.

00:20:13.208 --> 00:20:17.038
It was so gross and scary, I was frozen in place,

00:20:17.808 --> 00:20:19.378
but the boy from across the street...

00:20:19.378 --> 00:20:21.608
moved it to the flowerbed with a stick.

00:20:22.578 --> 00:20:24.018
I did that?

00:20:24.018 --> 00:20:27.388
Yes. You saved both of us, the earthworm and me.

00:20:28.788 --> 00:20:31.758
I fell for that kind-hearted boy from the very beginning.

00:20:32.118 --> 00:20:35.558
So I don't care what you become.

00:20:36.798 --> 00:20:40.268
Although, it is pretty fun that my stepmom hates it.

00:20:42.098 --> 00:20:45.338
If I fail again, I can't put it off. I'll have to enlist in the army.

00:20:46.908 --> 00:20:50.408
But I've always romanticized waiting for a boyfriend in the army.

00:20:56.548 --> 00:20:57.948
- Dad. - Oh, there you are.

00:20:59.118 --> 00:21:00.118
Have you eaten?

00:21:01.248 --> 00:21:02.418
Gosh, it's cold.

00:21:02.418 --> 00:21:03.418
(Junghu Academy)

00:21:06.628 --> 00:21:07.628
Dong Suk.

00:21:08.428 --> 00:21:11.358
The reason you don't want a divorce. It's because of Ji Hu, isn't it?

00:21:12.668 --> 00:21:13.828
That's right.

00:21:14.398 --> 00:21:15.798
Is there any other reason?

00:21:16.268 --> 00:21:20.138
No. I'm completely fed up with that man.

00:21:21.408 --> 00:21:23.538
Then stop torturing yourself...

00:21:24.478 --> 00:21:25.808
and divorce him.

00:21:27.078 --> 00:21:28.108
But...

00:21:30.278 --> 00:21:32.018
how am I supposed to raise Ji Hu on my own?

00:21:32.688 --> 00:21:36.688
What do you mean, on your own? We're all here to support you.

00:21:38.388 --> 00:21:43.058
You want Ji Hu to be a great doctor and inherit our clinic, right?

00:21:46.298 --> 00:21:47.798
I will personally make sure...

00:21:48.768 --> 00:21:51.138
that Ji Hu grows up to be the man you want him to be.

00:21:52.838 --> 00:21:55.308
- Se Ri. - So please, just...

00:21:55.878 --> 00:21:57.878
get off this sinking ship.

00:22:05.718 --> 00:22:06.848
Oh, Mom!

00:22:08.448 --> 00:22:09.458
- Hey. - Hello, ma'am.

00:22:09.488 --> 00:22:10.488
See you.

00:22:20.528 --> 00:22:22.538
You must be hungry. Go on, eat up.

00:22:27.338 --> 00:22:28.468
Eat up.

00:22:36.548 --> 00:22:37.548
Ji Hu.

00:22:39.348 --> 00:22:40.688
I...

00:22:43.388 --> 00:22:45.288
have something to tell you.

00:22:46.788 --> 00:22:47.928
Divorce Dad.

00:22:49.698 --> 00:22:50.728
I'm okay with it.

00:22:52.228 --> 00:22:55.228
You knew this whole time?

00:22:55.868 --> 00:22:57.538
Don't stay in this marriage for my sake.

00:22:58.398 --> 00:23:01.238
If you do, we'll all just be miserable.

00:23:02.638 --> 00:23:04.738
A lot of kids in my class have divorced parents.

00:23:05.408 --> 00:23:06.448
Nowadays,

00:23:07.378 --> 00:23:08.808
kids don't get teased for that anymore.

00:23:10.018 --> 00:23:11.118
Don't worry about me.

00:23:14.688 --> 00:23:16.888
My boy, you're all grown up.

00:23:18.058 --> 00:23:19.888
I feel like I haven't done anything for you.

00:23:24.958 --> 00:23:26.198
You should eat something too, Mom.

00:23:26.728 --> 00:23:28.398
You've been looking so drained lately.

00:23:33.208 --> 00:23:34.208
Okay, let's eat.

00:23:43.118 --> 00:23:44.378
What did you just say?

00:23:44.718 --> 00:23:46.618
You're saying Bucket's wife found out everything?

00:23:47.048 --> 00:23:49.888
Hush. He said it's the only way to resolve things over there.

00:23:50.358 --> 00:23:51.358
I suppose so.

00:23:53.158 --> 00:23:54.888
Anyway, this is so draining.

00:23:55.488 --> 00:23:59.198
When I ran into her in Ganghwa, I had to lie to cover things up,

00:23:59.428 --> 00:24:01.098
and now this is going to come back to bite me.

00:24:01.268 --> 00:24:05.468
- No, I'm sure she'll understand. - What?

00:24:05.768 --> 00:24:06.868
Are you taking her side now?

00:24:13.278 --> 00:24:16.518
Wow, so this is what you were out buying all day?

00:24:17.118 --> 00:24:19.318
Gosh, I feel so much better now that it's replaced.

00:24:19.818 --> 00:24:22.558
If I had it my way, I'd replace all the furniture too.

00:24:22.988 --> 00:24:27.058
Mom, what's wrong with it? It's still good. It'd be a waste.

00:24:27.128 --> 00:24:28.928
He's right. Mom, let's keep the furniture.

00:24:29.258 --> 00:24:31.128
I'll clean it all up and make it look brand new.

00:24:31.458 --> 00:24:32.458
All right!

00:24:50.248 --> 00:24:53.788
Oh, what's this cake for? Wow, this looks expensive.

00:24:53.918 --> 00:24:56.458
I bought it from the hotel for you, Uncle.

00:24:57.018 --> 00:24:59.658
Wow, that's my girl, Ju Ah.

00:25:00.658 --> 00:25:04.058
This is a party to celebrate your divorce!

00:25:06.068 --> 00:25:09.028
Hey, Ju Ah. You're really something else.

00:25:09.098 --> 00:25:13.368
We should celebrate his new start and his choice to be happier.

00:25:13.438 --> 00:25:16.238
That's right. What's not to celebrate?

00:25:16.308 --> 00:25:18.708
Come on, let's all be cool about this, okay?

00:25:18.708 --> 00:25:19.708
Yes, Mother.

00:25:19.708 --> 00:25:20.878
- I like the idea of being cool. - Yes.

00:25:20.948 --> 00:25:22.578
Good job, sweetie. Go on, light the candles.

00:25:23.318 --> 00:25:25.878
Uncle, once you blow these out...

00:25:25.948 --> 00:25:28.348
There! All your troubles will just disappear.

00:25:28.648 --> 00:25:30.218
- Just a moment. Goodness. - That's right.

00:25:30.288 --> 00:25:32.928
- I'll blow them out. Thank you. - Yes.

00:25:39.158 --> 00:25:41.168
But Dae Han,

00:25:41.668 --> 00:25:44.338
aren't you curious who she had the affair with?

00:25:44.398 --> 00:25:46.208
- Why would he be curious? - Hey!

00:25:46.738 --> 00:25:49.238
Do you always have to be such a buzz kill?

00:25:49.778 --> 00:25:54.408
- What? I thought this was cool. - That's not what being cool means.

00:25:54.408 --> 00:25:56.678
- Stop talking nonsense. Goodness. - Exactly.

00:25:56.748 --> 00:25:59.988
Seriously, why is everyone always ganging up on me? My gosh.

00:26:00.288 --> 00:26:04.058
Hey, Dae Han, why don't you go on a trip?

00:26:04.718 --> 00:26:07.688
- For a change of scenery. - No, the clinic's busy, so I can't.

00:26:07.758 --> 00:26:10.328
- No, you should go. Just go. - No, it's not that, Jeong Han.

00:26:10.928 --> 00:26:13.798
I'm not just pretending to be okay. I'm really fine.

00:26:14.298 --> 00:26:17.868
I'm sorry and a little embarrassed that I made you all worry,

00:26:18.498 --> 00:26:22.138
but I'm so grateful that you're all looking out for me.

00:26:22.208 --> 00:26:25.378
And because I have all of you, I'll be fine. Okay?

00:26:26.008 --> 00:26:30.448
Uncle, if you don't want a trip... Ta-da! How about a concert?

00:26:30.618 --> 00:26:31.618
Here you go.

00:26:32.378 --> 00:26:33.418
What's this?

00:26:34.448 --> 00:26:35.488
Let's see.

00:26:36.888 --> 00:26:38.118
Wow, awesome!

00:26:38.688 --> 00:26:40.488
Tickets to a 70s and 80s concert.

00:26:40.558 --> 00:26:42.958
- Nice. - What? Hey, there are two tickets.

00:26:42.958 --> 00:26:44.228
Who are you going to take?

00:26:44.298 --> 00:26:46.868
Well... Mom?

00:26:49.938 --> 00:26:53.738
Please. Count me out. Jeong Han is pouting. You two go.

00:26:53.808 --> 00:26:56.678
No, Mom. Look, your favourite singer, Yeo Jin, is in it.

00:26:56.738 --> 00:26:58.478
- He's right, Mom. - Really?

00:26:58.538 --> 00:26:59.548
Yes, here. Look.

00:27:00.978 --> 00:27:04.718
- My darling love, once so kind - Once so kind

00:27:04.778 --> 00:27:07.948
- Have you forgotten me? - Have you forgotten me?

00:27:08.318 --> 00:27:13.528
- Have you already forgotten me? - Have you already forgotten me?

00:27:14.888 --> 00:27:16.058
- Hey. Let's eat! - Yes, let's eat.

00:27:16.698 --> 00:27:18.158
- Yes, let's eat. - We're eating now?

00:27:18.228 --> 00:27:19.228
- Take out the candle. - All right.

00:27:19.298 --> 00:27:21.668
Hey. How did you even think of that?

00:27:21.828 --> 00:27:24.338
I know, right? How thoughtful.

00:27:24.898 --> 00:27:26.368
Hey, give it here. It's my cake.

00:27:34.548 --> 00:27:35.778
What is this?

00:27:38.278 --> 00:27:39.648
It's yerba mate.

00:27:39.848 --> 00:27:43.688
In Argentina, families share mate and drink from the same straw.

00:27:44.058 --> 00:27:46.328
It's a tradition that signifies trust and intimacy.

00:27:48.828 --> 00:27:53.598
I hoped by sharing this, you two could mend things.

00:27:54.868 --> 00:27:57.768
This will all blow over in time. You're being dramatic.

00:27:58.898 --> 00:28:00.368
All right, starting now.

00:28:00.968 --> 00:28:03.038
Hear each other out as you talk about what hurt you.

00:28:03.038 --> 00:28:05.108
Then take a sip of yerba mate...

00:28:05.178 --> 00:28:07.908
and say, "I see. So that's how you felt."

00:28:07.978 --> 00:28:09.718
All right, Dad, you can start!

00:28:14.518 --> 00:28:15.518
Go on.

00:28:18.258 --> 00:28:19.258
When I...

00:28:19.828 --> 00:28:21.328
was preparing for the election,

00:28:21.958 --> 00:28:25.158
- you know how hard I worked. - Eye contact, please.

00:28:29.168 --> 00:28:30.538
The fact that you voted for Jeong Han...

00:28:31.498 --> 00:28:33.768
- really hurt my feelings. - That's because you didn't...

00:28:33.768 --> 00:28:34.968
Grandpa, please.

00:28:35.638 --> 00:28:36.638
Here.

00:28:39.078 --> 00:28:40.078
Okay.

00:28:42.578 --> 00:28:43.948
I see.

00:28:45.178 --> 00:28:46.248
You did great.

00:28:46.618 --> 00:28:49.418
Okay, now it's your turn, Grandpa. Tell us what upset you.

00:28:52.118 --> 00:28:54.288
I went to see a doctor,

00:28:54.888 --> 00:28:56.998
but you cared about which doctor I saw,

00:28:56.998 --> 00:28:59.698
and not about what was wrong.

00:28:59.968 --> 00:29:02.428
- That really upset me. - That was...

00:29:02.838 --> 00:29:03.838
Here.

00:29:09.208 --> 00:29:13.008
I see, so that's how you felt. That's what upset you.

00:29:13.878 --> 00:29:16.478
I'm sorry. It's not that it didn't occur to me.

00:29:16.678 --> 00:29:18.048
I just wasn't myself at that moment.

00:29:19.318 --> 00:29:21.148
Okay, now it's your turn to say what upset you.

00:29:24.018 --> 00:29:25.018
Father.

00:29:25.518 --> 00:29:26.988
The way you've always...

00:29:27.628 --> 00:29:29.188
compared me to Jeong Han since I was young...

00:29:29.898 --> 00:29:32.498
and always calling me a good-for-nothing.

00:29:33.298 --> 00:29:35.598
- It's upsetting. - I see.

00:29:36.768 --> 00:29:40.138
I didn't realise I was doing that. I apologise.

00:29:40.768 --> 00:29:41.768
Okay.

00:29:42.208 --> 00:29:44.778
But does that give you the right to leave your old man to eat alone?

00:29:45.778 --> 00:29:47.378
That made me so upset.

00:29:50.278 --> 00:29:52.278
I'm sorry. I didn't realise you felt that way.

00:29:53.088 --> 00:29:55.248
Okay, now hold hands.

00:29:55.318 --> 00:29:56.818
Come on, give me your hands.

00:29:57.318 --> 00:30:01.428
Okay, repeat after me. "It's all good."

00:30:01.888 --> 00:30:04.558
- It's all good... - It's all good.

00:30:04.558 --> 00:30:05.658
Sir.

00:30:06.528 --> 00:30:07.598
Please don't do that again.

00:30:12.568 --> 00:30:13.568
You did great.

00:30:48.368 --> 00:30:53.248
Thank you for the gift. It really cheered everyone up.

00:30:54.778 --> 00:30:55.778
I'm glad to hear that.

00:31:01.818 --> 00:31:02.818
Oh, my.

00:31:05.558 --> 00:31:07.728
Don't tell me I woke you up.

00:31:08.888 --> 00:31:11.828
I just sent it so you'd see it in the morning.

00:31:13.828 --> 00:31:18.638
I couldn't sleep anyway. Dad and Grandpa are a snoring duo.

00:31:21.268 --> 00:31:25.878
I had something to tell you earlier, but I didn't get the chance.

00:31:27.248 --> 00:31:28.378
And what's that?

00:31:29.148 --> 00:31:31.618
You're not answering already, are you?

00:31:32.518 --> 00:31:35.048
I'm not going on that blind date tomorrow.

00:31:36.588 --> 00:31:38.988
You told me how you feel, and I kept you waiting.

00:31:39.088 --> 00:31:41.988
So it doesn't feel right to see someone else.

00:31:42.998 --> 00:31:44.058
Thank you.

00:31:45.158 --> 00:31:47.028
Good night, then.

00:31:52.038 --> 00:31:53.768
What does that mean?

00:31:54.238 --> 00:31:56.238
I'll see you in your dreams.

00:31:57.538 --> 00:31:58.608
Stay out of my dreams.

00:31:59.478 --> 00:32:00.748
Good night, then.

00:32:14.128 --> 00:32:15.128
Ten.

00:32:15.958 --> 00:32:17.128
Oh, boy.

00:32:18.058 --> 00:32:19.398
Be careful, Mom.

00:32:20.898 --> 00:32:22.928
Wow, take it easy. You'll hurt yourself.

00:32:24.268 --> 00:32:27.138
- Does it hurt? - No, I'm fine.

00:32:28.768 --> 00:32:30.678
Your hands have gotten so thin.

00:32:30.978 --> 00:32:32.608
- Look at this. - Oh, please.

00:32:32.608 --> 00:32:34.108
Go down.

00:32:35.178 --> 00:32:38.118
- Mom, be careful. Easy does it. - Come on up.

00:32:38.378 --> 00:32:39.378
That's it, up you go.

00:32:39.788 --> 00:32:44.418
- You did great. Now, go down. - Way to go, Mom! All the way.

00:32:44.488 --> 00:32:47.488
- Now, turn it slowly. - Five, six, seven.

00:33:02.038 --> 00:33:03.108
What is it, Mom?

00:33:03.378 --> 00:33:05.178
You think that man looks like Dad?

00:33:07.378 --> 00:33:11.278
I'm telling you, that other guy was his spitting image.

00:33:11.748 --> 00:33:13.048
Okay, Mom, that's enough.

00:33:13.648 --> 00:33:17.418
- No more trips to the police, okay? - All right, I'll stop.

00:33:19.558 --> 00:33:23.498
Man, it's been a while since the three of us did this.

00:33:24.258 --> 00:33:25.258
It really has.

00:33:25.528 --> 00:33:28.068
- We should do this more often. - Yes.

00:33:28.398 --> 00:33:29.528
Mom.

00:33:29.838 --> 00:33:33.908
Next week marks our 40th anniversary...

00:33:33.968 --> 00:33:35.668
of setting up here in Onjeong Market.

00:33:36.038 --> 00:33:37.938
Forty years? Has it really been that long?

00:33:38.438 --> 00:33:43.418
Our clinic and Dr. Yang's clinic are the oldest ones in the market.

00:33:45.178 --> 00:33:46.818
Forty years already...

00:33:57.498 --> 00:34:00.328
Here, dig in. I kept it simple today.

00:34:01.228 --> 00:34:04.768
- Eat up, Father. You too, honey. - Pasta for breakfast?

00:34:06.838 --> 00:34:09.508
Sitting side by side. Does that mean you two made up?

00:34:10.408 --> 00:34:11.408
Sit down.

00:34:11.708 --> 00:34:14.008
You seem thrilled you didn't have to cook today.

00:34:14.078 --> 00:34:15.978
Hey, you're on dish duty for that comment, Eun Bin.

00:34:17.978 --> 00:34:21.118
So Ji Hu's at his academy. Where are my aunt and uncle?

00:34:21.418 --> 00:34:23.818
They went out for brunch.

00:34:24.158 --> 00:34:25.658
Brunch?

00:34:26.388 --> 00:34:28.328
This looks delicious. Thank you for the meal!

00:34:36.498 --> 00:34:38.498
Why are you so dressed up?

00:34:39.198 --> 00:34:40.608
What's this about?

00:34:41.308 --> 00:34:43.408
I didn't want to look pathetic, especially not today.

00:34:51.818 --> 00:34:52.818
A divorce.

00:34:53.488 --> 00:34:54.888
Let's do it.

00:34:55.618 --> 00:34:56.888
Are you serious?

00:34:57.658 --> 00:35:00.428
- There are conditions. - Anything. Just name them.

00:35:00.728 --> 00:35:03.328
You need to work hard and send child support for Ji Hu.

00:35:03.498 --> 00:35:06.198
Of course, I will. I swear I'll work hard.

00:35:06.258 --> 00:35:08.268
On Ji Hu's birthday and for Christmas,

00:35:08.568 --> 00:35:10.468
make sure you send him a gift, even if it's just a gift card.

00:35:11.398 --> 00:35:15.738
You must attend his big events so he won't feel fatherless.

00:35:15.808 --> 00:35:17.778
Okay, yes! What else? Keep going!

00:35:18.338 --> 00:35:22.108
I am never going to date another man.

00:35:26.818 --> 00:35:28.388
So when our Ji Hu gets married...

00:35:31.788 --> 00:35:33.628
You have to come and sit in his father's place.

00:35:36.958 --> 00:35:38.058
And...

00:35:39.128 --> 00:35:41.728
spend at least one week with Ji Hu before you leave.

00:35:43.368 --> 00:35:45.968
About that... Yes, of course.

00:35:47.468 --> 00:35:49.168
And when you're with Ji Hu,

00:35:49.878 --> 00:35:51.708
don't you dare contact that woman.

00:35:54.178 --> 00:35:57.348
Right. Okay, I won't.

00:36:19.368 --> 00:36:20.868
So, why were we all called here?

00:36:21.268 --> 00:36:22.808
Is there some big announcement or what?

00:36:23.608 --> 00:36:26.978
The thing is...

00:36:27.048 --> 00:36:29.048
What trouble did you cause this time?

00:36:29.508 --> 00:36:34.048
- Well, it's... - I'll explain.

00:36:35.218 --> 00:36:39.318
He's leaving for Saudi Arabia this weekend.

00:36:39.418 --> 00:36:41.858
What? Saudi Arabia? Why, all of a sudden?

00:36:42.588 --> 00:36:46.328
Apparently, his friend started a construction supply business,

00:36:46.428 --> 00:36:51.298
and he asked him for help. It'll probably take a few years.

00:36:52.538 --> 00:36:54.068
Why, you...

00:36:57.378 --> 00:36:59.238
That's a smart move.

00:36:59.608 --> 00:37:00.978
After all your trouble,

00:37:01.378 --> 00:37:03.348
you're finally stepping up.

00:37:05.948 --> 00:37:07.518
When we were young, a lot of fathers...

00:37:07.518 --> 00:37:09.218
went to Saudi Arabia to make money.

00:37:09.348 --> 00:37:12.888
Someone from every other house went. To Saudi Arabia, Libya,

00:37:12.888 --> 00:37:16.698
- and Kuwait! - Auntie, is this really true?

00:37:17.158 --> 00:37:20.868
Yes, of course. It was a last-minute decision.

00:37:21.298 --> 00:37:22.298
So just leave it at that.

00:37:22.728 --> 00:37:24.168
Go over there and make a lot of money.

00:37:24.938 --> 00:37:26.768
It's a man's duty to provide for his wife and kids.

00:37:27.468 --> 00:37:28.868
And from now on, get your life together.

00:37:30.578 --> 00:37:31.578
I will.

00:37:42.448 --> 00:37:44.018
I'm a little worried about my aunt.

00:37:44.518 --> 00:37:46.688
I'll take good care of her. Don't you worry.

00:37:47.128 --> 00:37:50.328
Anyway, you couldn't even rest on the weekend. Thanks.

00:37:50.458 --> 00:37:53.128
I'm so glad your dad and grandpa made up, thanks to you.

00:37:53.568 --> 00:37:56.968
But Dad snores like a log. Does it bother you at night?

00:37:57.038 --> 00:37:58.968
I actually like it. It's like a lullaby to me.

00:38:02.338 --> 00:38:04.538
My gosh. Ji Hu.

00:38:18.158 --> 00:38:20.328
What was it like for you when your parents got divorced?

00:38:22.158 --> 00:38:23.728
It was tough.

00:38:25.358 --> 00:38:26.798
That's why, as you probably know,

00:38:27.598 --> 00:38:29.168
I ran away, pretending I was going to study abroad.

00:38:29.528 --> 00:38:30.968
I had to give up everything I loved.

00:38:32.898 --> 00:38:33.938
Do you regret it?

00:38:35.238 --> 00:38:36.238
Yes.

00:38:37.008 --> 00:38:38.008
That's why...

00:38:38.278 --> 00:38:40.448
I'm trying so hard to get it all back now.

00:38:41.408 --> 00:38:42.448
You're talking about a girl?

00:38:43.208 --> 00:38:44.218
Yes.

00:38:45.618 --> 00:38:47.818
What about you? You want to study abroad, too?

00:38:48.318 --> 00:38:50.358
No, I'm not going to.

00:38:50.958 --> 00:38:52.258
I'm going to stick it out here.

00:38:52.958 --> 00:38:54.158
To protect your mom?

00:38:55.358 --> 00:38:56.588
That's part of it,

00:38:57.158 --> 00:38:58.728
but I also don't want to break up with my girlfriend.

00:39:00.468 --> 00:39:01.468
Right.

00:39:02.198 --> 00:39:03.668
You're a lot better than I was.

00:39:04.268 --> 00:39:05.698
I'm sure you'll get through it just fine.

00:39:07.138 --> 00:39:08.138
I'll try my best.

00:39:18.578 --> 00:39:20.718
(Alarm)

00:39:23.788 --> 00:39:26.258
Gosh, you're up already?

00:39:29.158 --> 00:39:32.398
I have a shoot this week, so I have a lot to prep.

00:39:33.768 --> 00:39:38.438
Have Ju Ah drive for you sometimes. She always hitches a ride with you.

00:39:38.538 --> 00:39:40.368
Ju Ah has it tough, too.

00:39:42.408 --> 00:39:44.238
This is all your fault.

00:39:45.108 --> 00:39:48.178
Come on. How is this my fault now? Goodness.

00:39:48.348 --> 00:39:51.218
Things would've been so much better if we'd moved to Seoul like I said!

00:39:51.478 --> 00:39:54.648
If we'd moved, your sister-in-law wouldn't have had an affair.

00:39:55.248 --> 00:39:56.888
What? Why? How does that make sense?

00:39:57.158 --> 00:40:00.158
What, does her lover live here in Onjeong or something?

00:40:01.158 --> 00:40:02.628
I don't know.

00:40:03.528 --> 00:40:08.498
Gosh, I'm just sick and tired of you constantly fighting with Bucket.

00:40:09.498 --> 00:40:11.798
If we'd moved to Seoul, you would've made more money,

00:40:12.168 --> 00:40:13.768
and I wouldn't have had to do the TV show.

00:40:14.268 --> 00:40:17.038
Honestly, how could we have afforded to move to Seoul?

00:40:18.208 --> 00:40:19.478
So if we have the money, you'll move?

00:40:20.108 --> 00:40:21.508
We've paid off our loans,

00:40:21.778 --> 00:40:23.718
and I'll be getting paid once I sign my contract.

00:40:24.078 --> 00:40:28.988
Come on, you know clinics are scarce on the outskirts of Onjeong.

00:40:29.048 --> 00:40:30.958
Gosh, there he goes again.

00:40:31.958 --> 00:40:36.088
If I leave for Seoul too, who will care for the market people?

00:40:36.158 --> 00:40:40.628
And what younger doctor will want to come out to the boonies?

00:40:40.998 --> 00:40:43.068
Mother needs to get some rest, too.

00:40:43.198 --> 00:40:48.268
What? Mom's so young and healthy because she works.

00:40:48.268 --> 00:40:50.938
If she stops working, she'll age in a heartbeat.

00:40:51.638 --> 00:40:53.578
And the rumours about your brother's divorce...

00:40:54.208 --> 00:40:55.708
are going to be all over the market soon.

00:40:55.808 --> 00:40:59.648
So what? Divorce is no big deal. Besides, Dae Han has no kids.

00:40:59.718 --> 00:41:02.718
Frankly, we should spread the rumour so he can get remarried.

00:41:02.848 --> 00:41:05.958
And as the newly elected president, I'm already swamped.

00:41:06.058 --> 00:41:09.988
- What do you mean, move? - Gosh, I can't even look at you.

00:41:10.628 --> 00:41:12.128
- Go on, go back to sleep. - What?

00:41:12.528 --> 00:41:14.698
You know what? I think I will sleep a little more.

00:41:15.698 --> 00:41:20.668
- You smell nice. - Gosh, get away from me.

00:41:22.368 --> 00:41:24.178
Did you want to talk to me about something?

00:41:26.038 --> 00:41:27.048
What is it?

00:41:28.148 --> 00:41:32.848
The reason you lost the election isn't that I didn't vote for you.

00:41:33.448 --> 00:41:34.448
I know.

00:41:35.218 --> 00:41:39.558
- Because Jeong Han was better? - No. People just dislike you.

00:41:40.688 --> 00:41:42.558
Oh, I see.

00:41:44.028 --> 00:41:47.098
No, he's not saying that you're unlikeable.

00:41:47.368 --> 00:41:50.268
He just means you're perceived as unlikeable.

00:41:50.538 --> 00:41:54.008
When you hear even dogs hate you, that's something you have to fix.

00:41:54.238 --> 00:41:55.568
We can't have Councillor Hwang's people...

00:41:55.568 --> 00:41:57.108
hearing rumours like that.

00:41:57.608 --> 00:41:58.608
Exactly.

00:41:59.278 --> 00:42:02.978
Dr. Gong has already solidified his reputation as a friendly guy.

00:42:03.208 --> 00:42:05.248
So, compared to the association's president,

00:42:05.318 --> 00:42:08.388
you need an image as vice president who's more proactive.

00:42:08.448 --> 00:42:10.218
That's how you'll earn people's trust.

00:42:11.488 --> 00:42:13.628
That's my girl, Se Ri. That's exactly my point.

00:42:14.528 --> 00:42:17.458
A VP who's more proactive than the president.

00:42:18.098 --> 00:42:19.698
What do you think, honey? You can do it, right?

00:42:22.798 --> 00:42:24.768
- One, two, three, four. - One, two, three, four.

00:42:25.238 --> 00:42:28.208
- Five, six, seven, eight. - Five, six, seven, eight.

00:42:28.268 --> 00:42:30.838
- Two, two, three, four. - Two, two, three, four.

00:42:31.238 --> 00:42:33.778
- Five, six, seven, eight. - Five, six, seven, eight.

00:42:33.848 --> 00:42:36.178
Okay, leg forward and make a finger heart, all right?

00:42:36.378 --> 00:42:40.888
One, two, three, four. Now, blow it to your partner.

00:42:41.048 --> 00:42:44.958
Seven, eight. Switch feet. Two, two, three, four.

00:42:45.018 --> 00:42:48.858
Bigger smiles, everyone! One, two, seven, eight.

00:42:48.928 --> 00:42:50.828
Great. All right, shall we do some hip rotations?

00:42:51.658 --> 00:42:55.328
All right, great work, everyone.

00:42:56.028 --> 00:43:00.968
- All right, let's have another... - Have a healthy and profitable day!

00:43:01.168 --> 00:43:04.208
See you all again tomorrow. See you tomorrow!

00:43:04.908 --> 00:43:09.048
I'm going to finish cleaning up around Onjeong Market,

00:43:09.278 --> 00:43:11.178
and then I will start my clinic hours.

00:43:11.818 --> 00:43:15.818
All right, dismissed! I hope you all get rich!

00:43:16.618 --> 00:43:17.618
Yes!

00:43:18.618 --> 00:43:23.358
All right. Oh, man. Why so much trash everywhere?

00:43:23.958 --> 00:43:27.268
The sun's up in the sky

00:43:29.568 --> 00:43:30.568
What's gotten into him?

00:43:31.138 --> 00:43:32.538
What's with the sudden change of attitude?

00:43:32.868 --> 00:43:34.668
A sudden change in character means you're about to die.

00:43:34.668 --> 00:43:37.638
(Onjeong Market)

00:43:38.038 --> 00:43:41.278
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

00:43:44.148 --> 00:43:46.648
The situation appears resolved, thanks to our initial containment.

00:43:46.718 --> 00:43:48.788
No, we don't know that for sure.

00:43:49.288 --> 00:43:51.258
They say to always check for embers.

00:43:51.958 --> 00:43:52.958
Right.

00:43:57.958 --> 00:44:00.698
Oh, I heard Dr. Yang's sister is also getting a divorce.

00:44:01.768 --> 00:44:03.398
That's a relief.

00:44:03.898 --> 00:44:05.538
I was worried Hui Gyeong would cause a scene...

00:44:05.538 --> 00:44:07.308
if that man couldn't get a divorce.

00:44:08.208 --> 00:44:11.478
Wait, are you telling them all of our family business?

00:44:12.508 --> 00:44:16.348
No, of course not. It was just an emergency situation,

00:44:16.678 --> 00:44:18.118
so we were just exchanging information.

00:44:18.648 --> 00:44:20.448
All for the sake of peace between both families.

00:44:21.048 --> 00:44:25.358
Oh, dear. Anyway, I'm just so glad it all blew over quietly.

00:44:25.918 --> 00:44:26.918
Tell me about it.

00:44:29.628 --> 00:44:30.628
I'm exhausted.

00:44:31.828 --> 00:44:35.468
I get tired just thinking about the TV shoot.

00:44:36.668 --> 00:44:40.668
Mom, have you gotten any offers for commercials or anything?

00:44:41.308 --> 00:44:44.808
It seems like all the doctors on TV are doing commercials these days.

00:44:44.878 --> 00:44:48.448
Oh, please. The show is already killing me.

00:44:48.778 --> 00:44:49.778
Why do you ask?

00:44:50.248 --> 00:44:51.818
It's nothing, just wondering.

00:44:52.478 --> 00:44:55.648
Anyway, stay away from Bucket's kids.

00:44:56.588 --> 00:44:59.588
Astrologically speaking, our families are incompatible.

00:45:00.758 --> 00:45:02.628
What kind of doctor says something like that?

00:45:02.988 --> 00:45:05.758
- With no proof. - What do you mean there's no proof?

00:45:06.158 --> 00:45:09.628
The energy of the unconscious causes transference and compulsion,

00:45:09.698 --> 00:45:14.308
and even Freud wrote a paper on how that twists relationships.

00:45:15.408 --> 00:45:16.908
Anyway, just don't get close to them.

00:45:17.178 --> 00:45:18.178
Got it?

00:45:18.938 --> 00:45:22.748
Why would I? I hardly see them anyway.

00:45:23.548 --> 00:45:24.618
My gosh.

00:45:29.618 --> 00:45:31.458
You know this is the third time we're reviewing this, right?

00:45:32.118 --> 00:45:35.828
Right. So no typos, and the image cuts are fine.

00:45:36.688 --> 00:45:37.698
Go ahead and send it.

00:45:38.098 --> 00:45:40.358
- Really? Okay. - Yes.

00:45:43.268 --> 00:45:44.598
(Email sent successfully.)

00:45:45.898 --> 00:45:46.938
Sent!

00:45:47.968 --> 00:45:50.408
I really hope it goes well.

00:45:52.478 --> 00:45:55.908
Right. I'll make your mother a formal modelling offer.

00:45:57.478 --> 00:46:00.218
You'd probably save time looking for another model.

00:46:00.518 --> 00:46:01.548
She'll turn you down.

00:46:02.248 --> 00:46:04.018
But I really wish she would be our model.

00:46:04.858 --> 00:46:06.058
Why do you care so much?

00:46:06.988 --> 00:46:11.158
Your mother wearing your designs and walking the opening runway,

00:46:11.458 --> 00:46:14.768
and you two bowing at the finale... I think that would be wonderful.

00:46:22.808 --> 00:46:24.438
That does sound nice.

00:46:25.408 --> 00:46:26.538
She won't do it, though.

00:46:28.008 --> 00:46:30.518
Leave that to the company. We'll handle it.

00:46:33.918 --> 00:46:35.818
(Taehan)

00:46:36.188 --> 00:46:37.418
Good morning.

00:46:38.118 --> 00:46:39.118
What?

00:46:40.088 --> 00:46:41.328
What is all this?

00:46:43.088 --> 00:46:45.258
An atelier, just for you.

00:46:46.558 --> 00:46:49.628
I was worried helping with marketing would keep you from your real work,

00:46:50.468 --> 00:46:52.668
so I spruced this place up to help you stay inspired.

00:46:53.498 --> 00:46:54.538
Do you like it?

00:46:58.378 --> 00:46:59.378
I absolutely love it.

00:47:00.978 --> 00:47:02.248
Oh, my.

00:47:06.818 --> 00:47:07.818
This is amazing.

00:47:18.428 --> 00:47:23.368
Okay, these two outfits are our final entries for the contest,

00:47:23.728 --> 00:47:27.338
and if we get the platform deal, they'll be our main design samples.

00:47:28.208 --> 00:47:29.408
The execution is good,

00:47:29.968 --> 00:47:31.738
and the brand image is sophisticated,

00:47:32.138 --> 00:47:34.208
Overall, the quality is outstanding.

00:47:34.608 --> 00:47:35.648
Is there...

00:47:35.878 --> 00:47:38.148
any word from the platform yet?

00:47:38.918 --> 00:47:41.118
Pacu Nacho, you haven't told them yet?

00:47:43.548 --> 00:47:46.058
The proposal we submitted to Hyegyeong Department Store...

00:47:47.388 --> 00:47:49.658
received a very positive evaluation, thanks to Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

00:47:52.458 --> 00:47:55.828
Now, if we win the contest and secure the company's funding,

00:47:56.568 --> 00:48:00.368
Entry into Hyegyeong will be smooth, and our brand image will improve.

00:48:00.738 --> 00:48:03.108
So are we really getting into Hyegyeong?

00:48:04.078 --> 00:48:06.438
It's a bit early to pop the champagne,

00:48:07.238 --> 00:48:10.348
but there's nothing sweeter than popping it a little early.

00:48:11.448 --> 00:48:13.918
- Wow, look at that marbling. - The meat quality is unreal.

00:48:13.988 --> 00:48:16.388
Everyone, fill up your glasses.

00:48:16.848 --> 00:48:20.418
To Pacu Nacho and Ms. Gong for their hard work on the proposal.

00:48:20.888 --> 00:48:24.098
All right, shall we toast with our slogan?

00:48:24.498 --> 00:48:25.498
Shall we?

00:48:26.098 --> 00:48:30.128
- Return to FG! - Return to FG!

00:48:31.538 --> 00:48:33.968
- Great work, everyone! - Well done!

00:48:34.038 --> 00:48:37.308
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

00:48:38.478 --> 00:48:39.978
Wow, the food here is so good.

00:48:41.148 --> 00:48:43.508
He really is handsome.

00:48:43.678 --> 00:48:48.448
- Those forearms. So sexy. - Like this, you know?

00:48:49.648 --> 00:48:52.088
What are you two whispering about? Let me in on it.

00:48:53.488 --> 00:48:55.588
All the women on the marketing team these days...

00:48:56.828 --> 00:48:59.698
- are swooning over the Director. - Let's do this more often.

00:48:59.798 --> 00:49:01.528
The VP must be thrilled.

00:49:03.068 --> 00:49:04.768
- Should I grill the meat? - No, it's fine.

00:49:04.838 --> 00:49:06.668
- Are you sure? Really? - Yes.

00:49:08.068 --> 00:49:12.678
Here, eat something with that. Don't drink on an empty stomach, VP.

00:49:12.978 --> 00:49:13.978
I'm fine.

00:49:14.378 --> 00:49:16.008
Why don't you take care of someone over there?

00:49:17.148 --> 00:49:18.148
Come on.

00:49:18.518 --> 00:49:20.178
Vice President, let me pour you a drink.

00:49:22.888 --> 00:49:24.788
You must be very worried about the Chairman.

00:49:25.188 --> 00:49:26.888
It's the Chairman who's worried about me.

00:49:27.488 --> 00:49:28.888
That's why he's holding on.

00:49:31.098 --> 00:49:34.528
The moment my father passes, many people will come after me.

00:49:35.968 --> 00:49:37.938
It's a breath of fresh air coming to the Fashion Division.

00:49:38.238 --> 00:49:41.238
- Thanks for letting me join. - Of course. You're welcome anytime.

00:49:42.668 --> 00:49:44.778
- By the way, Mr. Park. - Yes?

00:49:45.808 --> 00:49:46.808
Ms. Gong.

00:49:52.878 --> 00:49:54.388
Don't they look like they're dating?

00:49:58.058 --> 00:50:00.218
Director, have some of this too.

00:50:00.728 --> 00:50:01.728
Thanks.

00:50:05.858 --> 00:50:07.998
Shouldn't we just wait and see?

00:50:09.128 --> 00:50:10.128
This is so exciting.

00:50:10.768 --> 00:50:12.798
Lately, watching those two is the highlight of my day at work.

00:50:39.358 --> 00:50:40.498
I've been looking all over for you.

00:50:41.268 --> 00:50:43.098
Why are you here all by yourself?

00:50:44.568 --> 00:50:48.968
Well, drinking always gives me the munchies for carbs.

00:50:55.578 --> 00:50:58.778
- Dipping bread in the soup? - What? Yes.

00:50:59.078 --> 00:51:00.078
Like fondue.

00:51:00.348 --> 00:51:04.288
And when you're done with that, you'll crush cookies in ice cream.

00:51:05.588 --> 00:51:08.258
Wow, you remember everything.

00:51:08.988 --> 00:51:11.058
You used to say I had the weirdest food cravings.

00:51:13.358 --> 00:51:16.398
Did your uncle get to the concert? It's today.

00:51:16.668 --> 00:51:19.138
Yes, he's sent me lots of pictures. He's having a blast.

00:51:19.668 --> 00:51:20.838
Thank you so much.

00:51:21.568 --> 00:51:25.008
Oh, right. Father... I mean, your father...

00:51:25.108 --> 00:51:27.078
I mean, Dr. Yang.

00:51:28.548 --> 00:51:31.218
You have a lot of names for him. What about my dad?

00:51:31.848 --> 00:51:35.788
I heard Dr. Yang has been working really hard lately.

00:51:36.048 --> 00:51:37.918
Yes, so I've heard.

00:51:38.718 --> 00:51:42.528
A project to fix his bad image, or so they say.

00:51:52.638 --> 00:51:53.668
All right.

00:51:55.108 --> 00:51:56.408
Take Gopyeong Market.

00:51:56.968 --> 00:51:59.938
After opening its night market, tourism soared,

00:52:00.038 --> 00:52:02.578
and sales tripled.

00:52:04.678 --> 00:52:07.618
But our goal for Onjeong Market...

00:52:08.388 --> 00:52:10.488
is a whopping fivefold increase in sales.

00:52:13.288 --> 00:52:16.128
I'm serious, everyone. A fivefold increase.

00:52:17.488 --> 00:52:19.798
More customers would be great for us, of course.

00:52:20.128 --> 00:52:23.168
- That would be amazing. - Yes, totally.

00:52:24.298 --> 00:52:26.168
- He's going overboard. - All right.

00:52:26.568 --> 00:52:28.568
- He's really laying it on thick. - So, what's the first step?

00:52:28.968 --> 00:52:30.568
We need to establish the infrastructure.

00:52:31.078 --> 00:52:35.078
Right? You all know this. Second, accessibility...

00:52:35.578 --> 00:52:39.948
All right, tell me your problems. I, Yang Dong Ik, will solve them.

00:52:40.118 --> 00:52:41.118
Go on, speak up.

00:52:41.488 --> 00:52:44.258
- The dumpsters are too far away. - Okay.

00:52:44.318 --> 00:52:46.688
- It's so hard to get to every time. - I'm sure that's been difficult.

00:52:46.758 --> 00:52:51.428
- Yes. - A central waste disposal area.

00:52:51.858 --> 00:52:53.728
Look into installing an additional one.

00:52:54.028 --> 00:52:56.568
- Okay, next. - There isn't enough parking.

00:52:56.568 --> 00:52:57.698
We need more parking spaces.

00:52:57.768 --> 00:52:58.938
You're right. We need that.

00:52:59.198 --> 00:53:02.838
Okay. A public parking lot nearby. Done.

00:53:02.838 --> 00:53:04.578
- Please add more restrooms. - Of course! We need those.

00:53:04.638 --> 00:53:06.638
- Can you help promote our market? - Promoting is my specialty.

00:53:06.878 --> 00:53:08.348
Please set up a lounge for the merchants.

00:53:08.348 --> 00:53:09.808
- That's right. - You don't have one?

00:53:09.878 --> 00:53:10.948
- Sure, we'll do it. - Please make it happen.

00:53:11.748 --> 00:53:12.748
Thank you.

00:53:18.088 --> 00:53:22.358
- Ji Hu's Dad is home. - He is?

00:53:23.058 --> 00:53:24.058
Thank goodness.

00:53:24.798 --> 00:53:25.798
Tell me about it.

00:53:26.658 --> 00:53:28.828
I guess I had it all wrong.

00:53:29.668 --> 00:53:30.668
That's good.

00:53:32.868 --> 00:53:34.098
I've decided to get a divorce.

00:53:38.278 --> 00:53:39.438
But...

00:53:39.938 --> 00:53:42.948
do you know who your wife had an affair with?

00:53:44.248 --> 00:53:45.248
I don't know.

00:53:45.678 --> 00:53:47.688
What good would it do to know? It would only hurt more.

00:53:50.918 --> 00:53:54.728
No way. It can't be. This is ridiculous.

00:53:57.188 --> 00:53:58.198
What's wrong?

00:53:58.928 --> 00:54:01.098
It's nothing.

00:54:15.548 --> 00:54:16.548
Oh, dear.

00:54:25.758 --> 00:54:28.428
- Oh, Mother. - Hey.

00:54:30.388 --> 00:54:34.158
Are you reviewing your script for the shoot today?

00:54:34.328 --> 00:54:37.128
Yes. Why are you up so early?

00:54:37.968 --> 00:54:40.338
- Did my light wake you? - No.

00:54:40.668 --> 00:54:43.438
No, I just had a nightmare,

00:54:43.838 --> 00:54:45.778
and I felt so stifled.

00:54:46.808 --> 00:54:50.078
It's chilly. Go back inside. Let me get you some tea. Okay?

00:54:50.148 --> 00:54:51.148
All right.

00:54:56.848 --> 00:54:57.858
What's wrong, Mother?

00:55:04.698 --> 00:55:06.258
Let's get rid of that.

00:55:08.898 --> 00:55:10.798
Yes, let's.

00:55:11.538 --> 00:55:12.768
I can't believe I didn't think of that.

00:55:24.418 --> 00:55:26.478
The call cannot be connected. You'll be connected to voicemail...

00:55:49.038 --> 00:55:50.938
(Hui)

00:55:51.008 --> 00:55:52.578
(Missed Call: Hui)

00:55:59.248 --> 00:56:01.518
- Hello? - You'll be connected to...

00:56:06.688 --> 00:56:10.028
Don't delude yourself into thinking he's going to love you forever.

00:56:10.658 --> 00:56:14.598
He might be sweet to you now, caught in the thrill of the affair,

00:56:14.998 --> 00:56:16.998
but will he be responsible...

00:56:17.428 --> 00:56:19.038
when he's married with a child?

00:56:22.538 --> 00:56:23.538
No...

00:56:31.778 --> 00:56:33.378
My gosh.

00:56:33.378 --> 00:56:36.948
I was waiting all week to hear about the brunch, ma'am.

00:56:40.288 --> 00:56:41.388
This...

00:56:42.358 --> 00:56:43.858
I feel a little funny taking this.

00:56:44.698 --> 00:56:46.198
Councillor Hwang's wife said...

00:56:46.198 --> 00:56:48.568
she feels uncomfortable about you joining us.

00:56:53.168 --> 00:56:54.608
I wonder why.

00:56:55.768 --> 00:56:58.138
You'd think she would at least tell me why.

00:57:00.138 --> 00:57:03.708
At the brunch, their daughter came along,

00:57:04.008 --> 00:57:05.518
and I remembered how you once said...

00:57:05.878 --> 00:57:08.488
you wanted to set her up with your son,

00:57:08.918 --> 00:57:12.258
so I just casually asked if she'd be up for a blind date.

00:57:13.688 --> 00:57:16.628
And Councillor Hwang's wife just flew off the handle.

00:57:16.628 --> 00:57:18.598
My gosh, why?

00:57:19.328 --> 00:57:22.828
Because you're Dr. Yang's second wife. She doesn't like that.

00:57:23.228 --> 00:57:24.498
She was dead serious about it.

00:57:29.008 --> 00:57:30.038
So, you're saying...

00:57:32.038 --> 00:57:34.708
It's not because of my husband...

00:57:36.548 --> 00:57:38.118
It's because of me?

00:57:38.618 --> 00:57:39.618
Yes.

00:57:40.018 --> 00:57:41.948
What Councillor Hwang values above all else...

00:57:42.218 --> 00:57:43.788
is the wife's standing.

00:57:44.148 --> 00:57:46.218
The reason he's trying so hard to get in with Dr. Gong...

00:57:46.688 --> 00:57:47.888
is because of his wife.

00:57:59.138 --> 00:58:02.138
You know her, right? Dr. Han Seong Mi from TV.

00:58:02.968 --> 00:58:04.978
She's a local celebrity in Onjeong.

00:58:06.108 --> 00:58:08.908
Frankly, you're a housewife and a second wife.

00:58:09.008 --> 00:58:10.878
You can't compare.

00:58:33.138 --> 00:58:34.468
We've been running into each other a lot lately.

00:58:35.608 --> 00:58:38.478
I have a show to tape this afternoon,

00:58:38.678 --> 00:58:40.838
so I'm getting my hair done before heading to the studio.

00:58:43.708 --> 00:58:45.918
So, are you transitioning into a full-time TV doctor?

00:58:46.718 --> 00:58:49.418
Then again, from what I saw in Ganghwa,

00:58:49.988 --> 00:58:51.558
you really know how to put on a show.

00:58:52.658 --> 00:58:54.058
Excuse me? A show?

00:58:54.928 --> 00:58:56.028
See you around.

00:58:59.398 --> 00:59:00.628
Gosh, that woman.

00:59:02.468 --> 00:59:04.198
We're just like oil and water.

00:59:09.468 --> 00:59:10.468
I will...

00:59:10.808 --> 00:59:13.038
drive her out of Onjeong for good.

00:59:15.978 --> 00:59:18.648
(Taehan Group)

00:59:22.788 --> 00:59:24.448
Wow! Who is this?

00:59:25.118 --> 00:59:28.388
Your bestie. I'm having lunch out today.

00:59:29.728 --> 00:59:33.628
Where are you having lunch all dressed up? What's the occasion?

00:59:46.978 --> 00:59:48.678
You're not upset that...

00:59:48.678 --> 00:59:50.848
I'm treating you to pork cutlets, are you?

00:59:52.578 --> 00:59:55.818
Did you forget? Pork cutlets are my favourite.

00:59:59.218 --> 01:00:03.628
So, what did you want to discuss over lunch?

01:00:06.028 --> 01:00:07.728
About what you asked me last time...

01:00:08.428 --> 01:00:10.098
I'm ready to give you my answer today.

01:00:23.048 --> 01:00:24.578
(Taxi)

01:00:28.918 --> 01:00:31.148
Oh, no. What is she doing here again?

01:00:38.828 --> 01:00:40.498
You look so beautiful today.

01:00:42.128 --> 01:00:46.468
On an important day, a woman dresses up for herself.

01:00:48.508 --> 01:00:50.368
After getting my hopes up like this,

01:00:51.308 --> 01:00:53.778
you're not about to turn me down, are you?

01:01:08.828 --> 01:01:11.658
What's all this? You all came out to see me off?

01:01:12.398 --> 01:01:14.928
- Have a safe trip, Uncle. - Yes, thanks.

01:01:17.328 --> 01:01:18.468
I'm off, honey.

01:01:18.938 --> 01:01:19.968
Okay.

01:01:21.868 --> 01:01:23.068
I'm off, Father.

01:01:23.668 --> 01:01:24.978
Here's some spending money.

01:01:25.608 --> 01:01:28.078
And call Dong Suk the minute you land in Saudi Arabia.

01:01:29.308 --> 01:01:31.008
Wow, thank you so much.

01:01:33.248 --> 01:01:36.648
You get to Saudi Arabia tomorrow, Korea time, right?

01:01:38.558 --> 01:01:39.558
Yes.

01:01:40.388 --> 01:01:41.388
Yes.

01:01:41.888 --> 01:01:42.888
Saudi Arabia?

01:01:46.358 --> 01:01:48.398
What the... Isn't that Gong Dae Han's wife?

01:01:49.928 --> 01:01:52.238
Are you abandoning me and going to Saudi Arabia?

01:01:52.868 --> 01:01:56.138
You were just going to leave me and run off like that, darling?

01:01:56.208 --> 01:01:57.468
- No, it's not like that... - "Darling?"

01:01:57.538 --> 01:01:58.778
- It's not like that. - Excuse me.

01:01:59.008 --> 01:02:00.038
Hey, you!

01:02:00.508 --> 01:02:02.348
- Hui Gyeong. - I...

01:02:02.408 --> 01:02:05.078
- What are you doing? Let's go. - No...

01:02:05.348 --> 01:02:06.348
Wait a minute.

01:02:07.078 --> 01:02:08.118
Hold on.

01:02:08.648 --> 01:02:10.188
What did you just say to him?

01:02:10.788 --> 01:02:11.788
"Darling?"

01:02:11.988 --> 01:02:15.228
It's not what you think, Dong Suk. What're you doing? Go on, take her!

01:02:15.288 --> 01:02:16.358
What in the world is going on?

01:02:16.688 --> 01:02:20.358
So much drama! Grandpa, my eyes are about to pop out.

01:02:20.498 --> 01:02:23.328
Eun Bin, take Grandfather inside right now. Hurry.

01:02:23.398 --> 01:02:25.698
- Let's go talk somewhere else. - Let go of me!

01:02:26.238 --> 01:02:30.568
I'm not going anywhere without you. Darling, say something!

01:02:30.668 --> 01:02:33.678
- No, it's not... Look. - Hey!

01:02:36.178 --> 01:02:37.948
So the witch having an affair with my husband...

01:02:39.148 --> 01:02:40.878
was you? Gong Dae Han's wife?

01:02:43.188 --> 01:02:44.248
That's right. It was me!

01:02:44.688 --> 01:02:47.288
I'm the one your husband really loves.

01:02:48.558 --> 01:02:49.558
Shut it!

01:02:51.058 --> 01:02:52.558
Nice one, Auntie!

01:02:54.028 --> 01:02:56.768
Darling! Are you okay?

01:02:57.398 --> 01:02:59.638
- Hey! - Goodness, this is a disaster.

01:02:59.698 --> 01:03:00.898
- You witch. - Let go!

01:03:01.068 --> 01:03:04.008
Only one of us is walking away from this.

01:03:04.308 --> 01:03:06.008
- I'm going to kill them both! - Don't!

01:03:06.208 --> 01:03:09.308
- I'm going to kill you both today! - Stop it!

01:03:09.378 --> 01:03:10.508
Please, stop.

01:03:14.718 --> 01:03:15.948
Goodness. Oh, no.

01:03:16.848 --> 01:03:17.848
I can't believe this...

01:03:48.418 --> 01:03:51.348
(Recipe for Love)

01:03:51.418 --> 01:03:53.988
Is it true your husband's having an affair with Gong Dae Han's wife?

01:03:54.488 --> 01:03:56.958
Hey! Gong Jeong Han! Gong Dae Han! Get out here!

01:03:56.958 --> 01:03:59.698
- I'll go out. You stay put. - Feel better now?

01:03:59.798 --> 01:04:02.728
I have to blame someone, or I feel like I'm going to die.

01:04:04.768 --> 01:04:08.668
Where did you drag her from? I want to kill that jerk.

01:04:09.508 --> 01:04:14.008
I went to a good psychic. She said to stay away from the Gongs.

01:04:14.078 --> 01:04:15.078
The Gongs?

01:04:15.148 --> 01:04:18.678
I'm so worried that our kids are going to get dragged into this.

01:04:18.748 --> 01:04:21.888
I will never let that happen.

01:04:22.048 --> 01:04:24.988
It's best for our two families to part ways, right?

01:04:25.418 --> 01:04:27.988
It's time to finally break this toxic connection.